search:Advanced Error Handling in React-.content:
- Install `@react-native-firebase/app` and `@react-native-firebase/auth`.
- Use `firebase.auth().signInWithEmailAndPassword(email, password)` for authentication.
- Handle errors using try-catch blocks.
- Display custom alerts with error codes:
  ```javascript
  switch (error.code) {
    case 'auth/invalid-email':
      alert('The email address is invalid.');
      break;
    case 'auth/user-not-found':
      alert('No user found with this email.');
      break;
    case 'auth/wrong-password':
      alert('Wrong password provided.');
      break;
    default:
      alert('An error occurred. Please try again later.');
  }
  ```
- Ensure Firebase is properly configured in your project.
- Update dependencies regularly using `npm update` or `yarn upgrade`.
